# HMO Plugin — Git commits and GitHub releases

Follow this whenever shipping changes to **this repository** (Hostlinks Marketing Ops). The plugin auto-updater reads **GitHub Releases** (`releases/latest`) and the **`hostlinks-marketing-ops.zip`** asset.

## Repository root

This folder is the Git repo root: it contains `hostlinks-marketing-ops.php`, `.github/workflows/`, etc.

Remote: `https://github.com/spkldbrd/hostlinks-marketing-ops` (branch: `main`)

Run all **git** and **release** commands from this directory (or pass `-C` to that path).

---

## Step 1 — Bump the version

Edit **two places** in `hostlinks-marketing-ops.php`:

```php
 * Version:     1.4.5   ← plugin header
...
define( 'HMO_VERSION',    '1.4.5' );   ← constant (spacing as in file)
```

Only bump **`HMO_DB_VERSION`** when a database schema change is included.

Optionally add a line under `== Changelog ==` in `readme.txt` for the same version.

---

## Step 2 — Commit and push (PowerShell)

**Do not use `&&` or heredoc (`<<'EOF'`) — not valid in Windows PowerShell.**

With this repo as the Cursor workspace root, `(Get-Location).Path` is the plugin root. Otherwise set `$PluginRoot` to your clone path.

```powershell
$PluginRoot = (Get-Location).Path   # or: "C:\path\to\hostlinks-marketing-ops"
Set-Location $PluginRoot
$msg = "fix: short description of change (v1.X.X)"
git add -A
git commit -m $msg
git push origin main
```

Use **Conventional-commit** prefixes when they fit (`fix:`, `feat:`, `ci:`, etc.) and include the version when helpful (e.g. `(v1.4.6)`).

---

## Step 3 — Release zip and GitHub Release (default: automated)

Pushing to **`main`** runs GitHub Actions: [`.github/workflows/release-zip.yml`](.github/workflows/release-zip.yml)

- Reads **`HMO_VERSION`** from `hostlinks-marketing-ops.php`
- Builds **`hostlinks-marketing-ops.zip`** with root folder `hostlinks-marketing-ops/` and Unix-style paths (Linux-safe)
- **Creates** the GitHub Release + tag if missing, or **`gh release upload --clobber`** if the release already exists (same version, refreshed zip)

After push, confirm on GitHub: **Actions** (workflow succeeded) and **Releases** (zip attached). The updater cache busts when admins visit the Marketing Ops settings page.

**Agents:** after a version bump, commit and push from this repo. **Do not skip the push** — it triggers the release workflow.

---

## Step 4 — Manual zip + release (fallback only)

Use when Actions failed, are disabled, or you must ship without waiting for CI.

### 4a — Build the zip (.NET `ZipFile`, forward slashes)

Always use **.NET `ZipFile`** so zip entries use **forward slashes** (required on Linux). **Do not use `Compress-Archive`** — it can produce backslashes that break extraction on the host.

```powershell
$PluginRoot = (Get-Location).Path   # repo root = folder with hostlinks-marketing-ops.php
$zipPath   = Join-Path (Split-Path $PluginRoot -Parent) "hostlinks-marketing-ops.zip"

if (Test-Path $zipPath) { Remove-Item $zipPath -Force }

Add-Type -AssemblyName System.IO.Compression.FileSystem
$zip = [System.IO.Compression.ZipFile]::Open($zipPath, 'Create')

Get-ChildItem -Path $PluginRoot -Recurse -File | Where-Object {
    $_.FullName -notmatch '[\\/]\.git[\\/]'
} | ForEach-Object {
    $relative = $_.FullName.Substring($PluginRoot.Length + 1).Replace('\', '/')
    $entry    = "hostlinks-marketing-ops/$relative"
    [System.IO.Compression.ZipFileExtensions]::CreateEntryFromFile($zip, $_.FullName, $entry, 'Optimal') | Out-Null
}

$zip.Dispose()
```

The zip root folder must be **`hostlinks-marketing-ops/`** so WordPress installs correctly.

### 4b — Create or refresh the GitHub release

```powershell
Set-Location $PluginRoot
gh release create 1.X.X $zipPath `
    --title "v1.X.X - Short title" `
    --notes "What changed in this release."
```

If the release exists and you only replace the asset:

```powershell
gh release upload 1.X.X $zipPath --clobber
```

